                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <head>[Translation.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, D. C.,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1903</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Diehl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Boston:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Upon the arrival of the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> sufficient force must
                    be sent to watch movements closely of the British steamers seized at
                    Buenaventura and to prevent the landing of men with hostile intent within limits
                    of the State of Panama. Protect the British steamers if necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moody.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
